  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'When should I take sleep gummies?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Take melatonin sleep gummies 30 to 60 minutes before your target bedtime. Melatonin works by signaling your circadian clock that it is time for sleep, not by sedating you directly. Taking it too early may shift your sleep schedule. L-theanine and magnesium gummies can also be taken 30 to 60 minutes before bed. For optimal results, combine sleep gummies with consistent timing — take them at the same time every night to reinforce your circadian rhythm.' } },
  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Do sleep gummies cause morning grogginess?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Morning grogginess (sleep inertia) from sleep gummies is typically caused by melatonin doses that are too high. Doses above 5mg are more likely to cause residual drowsiness. Lower doses (0.5 to 3mg) are less likely to produce this effect. If you experience morning grogginess, reduce your melatonin dose or switch to a non-melatonin formula using L-theanine, magnesium, or chamomile, which promote sleep quality without the hormone-based mechanism that can cause carryover drowsiness.' } },
